#### 1. Component-Level Documentation
```tsx
// ---
// HOW TO EDIT THE SIZE OF THE WHOLE RADAR CHART?
// ---
// The size of the radar chart is controlled by two main things:
// 1. The height of the container div (e.g. className="h-[350px]")
//    - This controls the vertical space for the chart. Increase/decrease the h-[XXXpx] value to make the chart area taller or shorter.
// 2. The `outerRadius` prop on the <RadarChart /> component (e.g. outerRadius="60%")
//    - This controls the radius of the radar chart as a percentage of the container. Increase to make the chart fill more of the container, decrease for more padding.
// 
// To make the chart bigger or smaller, change the value of the container's height
// and/or the `outerRadius` prop. Both are set separately for mobile and desktop below.
// ---
```

